## Reflection
Governance is just as important as technical skill because it provides the "rules of the road" for how technology is used. While a technical skill allows me to set up a GitHub repository, governance (in the form of the AAA framework) determines who has the permission to push code and how that access is logged. Without these frameworks, technical security would be disorganized and difficult to verify. The cybersecurity domain that aligns most with today’s material is **GRC (Governance, Risk, and Compliance)**. This lab specifically highlights the "Compliance" and "Accounting" aspects of maintaining a professional technical workbench.

